.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Query data.
( Suppose the specific collection space named "foo" existes and the current
sequoiadb is started in standalone mode )
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.find()
{
\ \ \ "_id":\ {
\ \ \ \ \ "$oid":\ "5d36c9d5c6b1cee56abefc7e"
\ \ \ },
\ \ \ "name":\ "fang",
\ \ \ "age":\ 18
}
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Unload the collection space named foo from memory.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.unloadCS(\ "foo"\ )
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Query data.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.find()
uncaught\ exception:\ \-34
Collection\ space\ does\ not\ exist
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Load the collection space named into memory.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.loadCS(\ "foo"\ )
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Query data again.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.find()
{
\ \ \ "_id":\ {
\ \ \ \ \ "$oid":\ "5d36c9d5c6b1cee56abefc7e"
\ \ \ },
\ \ \ "name":\ "fang",
\ \ \ "age":\ 18
}
\f[]
